{"id": "EUVD-2025-12950", "enisaUuid": "e3667707-3b26-3ef9-9641-ffb34831fb00", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: mhi: Fix memory leak in mhi_net_dellink()\n\nMHI driver registers network device without setting the\nneeds_free_netdev flag, and does NOT call free_netdev() when\nunregisters network device, which causes a memory leak.\n\nThis patch calls free_netdev() to fix it since netdev_priv\nis used after unregister.", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T15:31:48", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-07T21:31:19", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49817", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/25a270343b0f16e1f6e65f541a15975a35e238ff", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/88da008e5e2f9753726ea5a51ef2eb144e9de927", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f7c125bd79f50ec6094761090be81d02726ec6f4"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49817", "GHSA-vxf7-8458-rq8x"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0b60350f-6ce8-3dd9-b74c-8f37d58d6735", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "13adac032982c61bb590669e8e87e51558917ca1 <f7c125bd79f50ec6094761090be81d02726ec6f4"}, {"id": "1888e173-7ad0-335b-adf1-010ab9720fba", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "1b47183b-7eba-395f-a66d-cc99845fc81c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.14"}, {"id": "1c572f1d-7b8f-356e-b1fa-28e2c98a57a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3bb088cd-5bdd-3bb0-b166-d9434b5c16c9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "13adac032982c61bb590669e8e87e51558917ca1 <88da008e5e2f9753726ea5a51ef2eb144e9de927"}, {"id": "4720a1a7-9b59-322f-98ed-eca09dd719bf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "13adac032982c61bb590669e8e87e51558917ca1 <25a270343b0f16e1f6e65f541a15975a35e238ff"}, {"id": "82aac11f-c406-31c9-ad8b-043311192835", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.80"}, {"id": "d58021de-c4bb-309e-a8e